opps.description:
NOAA/NMFS seeks a qualified GSA Multiple Award Schedule contractor under SIN 561920 and/or 561510 to provide American Fisheries Advisory Committee (AFAC) Logistics, Travel, and Meeting Support. This requirement is a 100% small business set-aside and contemplates award of one order with a base period and four option periods.

The contractor shall provide end-to-end planning, coordination, and administrative support for AFAC meetings. The Government anticipates three meetings per performance period: two in-person AFAC meetings (typically in April and September, up to four business days each) at rotating AFAC regional locations, and one virtual AFAC meeting (approximately four hours). Planning and virtual support will occur at the contractor's facility; on-site support for in-person meetings will occur at the meeting location.

Required services include, at a minimum:
(1) meeting facility coordination and logistics for in-person meetings, including hotel/facility sourcing, room blocks, conference space, AV/equipment, seating/microphones, internet, projection/laptop connectivity, power, required meeting refreshments, and participant materials/folders;
(2) development of an objective Venue and Approved Direct Meeting Cost Solution Package for each in-person meeting, including at least three technically acceptable complete solutions using common assumptions, whole-price total meeting cost comparisons, identification of fees/credits/rebates/allowances, and separation of Participant Travel assumptions from Approved Direct Meeting Costs;
(3) participant travel coordination and reimbursement administration for authorized non-Federal participants, including flight/lodging coordination, receipt/invoice collection, reimbursement review, per diem ceiling application, airfare comparison, deficiency/rejection notices, dispute handling, and post-conference reimbursement reporting;
