Background
 The National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), specifically the Office of Marine & Aviation Operations (OMAO), is seeking to procure husbandry services for the NOAA Ship Pisces while it is docked at Las Palmas de Gran Canaria, Spain. 

The goal of this contract is to ensure that the ship receives necessary logistical support during its stay in port, which includes a variety of services essential for the ship's operations and crew welfare.

